# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cloudflare Access scaffolding — NOT loaded (.tf.example). Rename to access.tf to activate, then add
# the matching variables (allow_email) and `tofu apply`. The provided token already has the Access
# scopes. Per the lab's per-host policy, MOST hosts should NOT get an interactive Access app:
#
#   home.chifor.me     -> already SSO-gated by oauth2-proxy/Authelia; no app (would be a double login)
#   sso.chifor.me      -> the Authelia IdP itself; MUST NOT get an app (deadlocks every OIDC flow)
#   chat / grafana     -> Authelia OIDC clients already; leave to Authelia (Bypass if an app must exist)
#   api.chifor.me      -> machine API; ONLY a Service Token / non_identity policy, never interactive
#   status.chifor.me   -> the one host worth an interactive Allow app, IF you want it private
#
# So the only sensible interactive app is `status` (below), and the only sensible API gate is the
# api service token (below). Everything else stays with Authelia.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# variable "allow_email" {
#   description = "Cloudflare Access allow-list email for interactively-gated hosts."
#   type        = string
# }

# --- Optional: gate status.chifor.me with an interactive Allow policy (your email) ---
# resource "cloudflare_zero_trust_access_policy" "allow_me" {
